{"id":83030,"title":"SLE and dental erosion: a lethal cocktail.","abstract":"A 13-year-old Pacific Island girl presented complaining of fever, joint pain and dry mouth. She was using limes to relieve her dry mouth. On examination, the most striking clinical finding was severe dental erosion and caries. Autoimmune serology confirmed a diagnosis of systemic lupus erythematosus (SLE) with possible Sj√∂gren's syndrome. The case illustrates the devastating consequence of excessive consumption of acidic citrus juice in sicca syndrome. ","date":"2014-03-20","categories":"Stomatognathic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24464153","annotations":[{"name":"Pain","weight":0.801843,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pain"},{"name":"Systemic lupus erythematosus","weight":0.791621,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Systemic_lupus_erythematosus"},{"name":"Autoimmunity","weight":0.787846,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Autoimmunity"},{"name":"Mouth","weight":0.750806,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mouth"},{"name":"Serology","weight":0.735177,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serology"},{"name":"Joint","weight":0.729313,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joint"},{"name":"Fever","weight":0.71741,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fever"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.714354,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Arthralgia","weight":0.609736,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arthralgia"},{"name":"Xerostomia","weight":0.563854,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Xerostomia"},{"name":"Tuberculosis","weight":0.516195,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tuberculosis"},{"name":"Lupus erythematosus","weight":0.445723,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lupus_erythematosus"},{"name":"Acid","weight":0.440985,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/A